25/*
26 * Tree building functions
27 */
28
29void add_label(struct label **labels, char *label)
30{
31 struct label *new;
32
33 /* Make sure the label isn't already there */
34 for_each_label_withdel(*labels, new)
35 if (streq(new->label, label)) {
36 new->deleted = 0;
37 return;
38 }
39
40 new = xmalloc(sizeof(*new));
41 memset(new, 0, sizeof(*new));
42 new->label = label;
43 new->next = *labels;
44 *labels = new;
45}
46
47void delete_labels(struct label **labels)
48{
49 struct label *label;
50
51 for_each_label(*labels, label)
52 label->deleted = 1;
53}
54
55struct property *build_property(char *name, struct data val)
56{
57 struct property *new = xmalloc(sizeof(*new));
58
59 memset(new, 0, sizeof(*new));
60
61 new->name = name;
62 new->val = val;
63
64 return new;
65}
66
67struct property *build_property_delete(char *name)
68{
69 struct property *new = xmalloc(sizeof(*new));
70
71 memset(new, 0, sizeof(*new));
72
73 new->name = name;
74 new->deleted = 1;
75
76 return new;
77}
78
79struct property *chain_property(struct property *first, struct property *list)
80{
81 assert(first->next == NULL);
82
83 first->next = list;
84 return first;
85}
86
87struct property *reverse_properties(struct property *first)
88{
89 struct property *p = first;
90 struct property *head = NULL;
91 struct property *next;
92
93 while (p) {
94 next = p->next;
95 p->next = head;
96 head = p;
97 p = next;
98 }
99 return head;
100}
101
102struct node *build_node(struct property *proplist, struct node *children)
103{
104 struct node *new = xmalloc(sizeof(*new));
105 struct node *child;
106
107 memset(new, 0, sizeof(*new));
108
109 new->proplist = reverse_properties(proplist);
110 new->children = children;
111
112 for_each_child(new, child) {
113 child->parent = new;
114 }
115
116 return new;
117}
118
119struct node *build_node_delete(void)
120{
121 struct node *new = xmalloc(sizeof(*new));
122
123 memset(new, 0, sizeof(*new));
124
125 new->deleted = 1;
126
127 return new;
128}

130struct node *name_node(struct node *node, char *name)
131{
132 assert(node->name == NULL);
133
134 node->name = name;
135
136 return node;

139struct node *merge_nodes(struct node *old_node, struct node *new_node)
140{
141 struct property *new_prop, *old_prop;
142 struct node *new_child, *old_child;
143 struct label *l;
144
145 old_node->deleted = 0;
146
147 /* Add new node labels to old node */
148 for_each_label_withdel(new_node->labels, l)
149 add_label(&old_node->labels, l->label);
150
151 /* Move properties from the new node to the old node. If there
152 * is a collision, replace the old value with the new */
153 while (new_node->proplist) {
154 /* Pop the property off the list */
155 new_prop = new_node->proplist;
156 new_node->proplist = new_prop->next;
157 new_prop->next = NULL;
158
159 if (new_prop->deleted) {
160 delete_property_by_name(old_node, new_prop->name);
161 free(new_prop);
162 continue;
163 }
164
165 /* Look for a collision, set new value if there is */
166 for_each_property_withdel(old_node, old_prop) {
167 if (streq(old_prop->name, new_prop->name)) {
168 /* Add new labels to old property */
169 for_each_label_withdel(new_prop->labels, l)
170 add_label(&old_prop->labels, l->label);
171
172 old_prop->val = new_prop->val;
173 old_prop->deleted = 0;
174 free(new_prop);
175 new_prop = NULL;
176 break;
177 }
178 }
179
180 /* if no collision occurred, add property to the old node. */
181 if (new_prop)
182 add_property(old_node, new_prop);
183 }
184
185 /* Move the override child nodes into the primary node. If
186 * there is a collision, then merge the nodes. */
187 while (new_node->children) {
188 /* Pop the child node off the list */
189 new_child = new_node->children;
190 new_node->children = new_child->next_sibling;
191 new_child->parent = NULL;
192 new_child->next_sibling = NULL;
193
194 if (new_child->deleted) {
195 delete_node_by_name(old_node, new_child->name);
196 free(new_child);
197 continue;
198 }
199
200 /* Search for a collision. Merge if there is */
201 for_each_child_withdel(old_node, old_child) {
202 if (streq(old_child->name, new_child->name)) {
203 merge_nodes(old_child, new_child);
204 new_child = NULL;
205 break;
206 }
207 }
208
209 /* if no collision occurred, add child to the old node. */
210 if (new_child)
211 add_child(old_node, new_child);
212 }
213
214 /* The new node contents are now merged into the old node. Free
215 * the new node. */
216 free(new_node);
217
218 return old_node;
219}

221struct node *chain_node(struct node *first, struct node *list)
222{
223 assert(first->next_sibling == NULL);
224
225 first->next_sibling = list;
226 return first;
227}
228
229void add_property(struct node *node, struct property *prop)
230{
231 struct property **p;
232
233 prop->next = NULL;
234
235 p = &node->proplist;
236 while (*p)
237 p = &((*p)->next);
238
239 *p = prop;
240}
241
242void delete_property_by_name(struct node *node, char *name)
243{
244 struct property *prop = node->proplist;
245
246 while (prop) {
247 if (streq(prop->name, name)) {
248 delete_property(prop);
249 return;
250 }
251 prop = prop->next;
252 }
253}
254
255void delete_property(struct property *prop)
256{
257 prop->deleted = 1;
258 delete_labels(&prop->labels);
259}
260
261void add_child(struct node *parent, struct node *child)
262{
263 struct node **p;
264
265 child->next_sibling = NULL;
266 child->parent = parent;
267
268 p = &parent->children;
269 while (*p)
270 p = &((*p)->next_sibling);
271
272 *p = child;
273}
274
275void delete_node_by_name(struct node *parent, char *name)
276{
277 struct node *node = parent->children;
278
279 while (node) {
280 if (streq(node->name, name)) {
281 delete_node(node);
282 return;
283 }
284 node = node->next_sibling;
285 }
286}
287
288void delete_node(struct node *node)
289{
290 struct property *prop;
291 struct node *child;
292
293 node->deleted = 1;
294 for_each_child(node, child)
295 delete_node(child);
296 for_each_property(node, prop)
297 delete_property(prop);
298 delete_labels(&node->labels);
299}
300
301void append_to_property(struct node *node,
302 char *name, const void *data, int len)
303{
304 struct data d;
305 struct property *p;
306
307 p = get_property(node, name);
308 if (p) {
309 d = data_append_data(p->val, data, len);
310 p->val = d;
311 } else {
312 d = data_append_data(empty_data, data, len);
313 p = build_property(name, d);
314 add_property(node, p);
315 }
316}

320 struct reserve_info *new = xmalloc(sizeof(*new));

322 memset(new, 0, sizeof(*new));

324 new->address = address;
325 new->size = size;
326
327 return new;

330struct reserve_info *chain_reserve_entry(struct reserve_info *first,
331 struct reserve_info *list)
332{
333 assert(first->next == NULL);
334
335 first->next = list;
336 return first;
337}
338
339struct reserve_info *add_reserve_entry(struct reserve_info *list,
340 struct reserve_info *new)
341{
342 struct reserve_info *last;
343
344 new->next = NULL;
345
346 if (! list)
347 return new;
348
349 for (last = list; last->next; last = last->next)
350 ;
351
352 last->next = new;
353
354 return list;
355}

357struct dt_info *build_dt_info(unsigned int dtsflags,
358 struct reserve_info *reservelist,
359 struct node *tree, uint32_t boot_cpuid_phys)
360{
361 struct dt_info *dti;
362
363 dti = xmalloc(sizeof(*dti));
364 dti->dtsflags = dtsflags;
365 dti->reservelist = reservelist;
366 dti->dt = tree;
367 dti->boot_cpuid_phys = boot_cpuid_phys;
368
369 return dti;
370}

376const char *get_unitname(struct node *node)
377{
378 if (node->name[node->basenamelen] == '\0')
379 return "";
380 else
381 return node->name + node->basenamelen + 1;
382}
383
384struct property *get_property(struct node *node, const char *propname)
385{
386 struct property *prop;
387
388 for_each_property(node, prop)
389 if (streq(prop->name, propname))
390 return prop;
391
392 return NULL;
393}
394
395cell_t propval_cell(struct property *prop)
396{
397 assert(prop->val.len == sizeof(cell_t));
398 return fdt32_to_cpu(*((fdt32_t *)prop->val.val));
399}
400
401struct property *get_property_by_label(struct node *tree, const char *label,
402 struct node **node)
403{
404 struct property *prop;
405 struct node *c;
406
407 *node = tree;
408
409 for_each_property(tree, prop) {
410 struct label *l;
411
412 for_each_label(prop->labels, l)
413 if (streq(l->label, label))
414 return prop;
415 }
416
417 for_each_child(tree, c) {
418 prop = get_property_by_label(c, label, node);
419 if (prop)
420 return prop;
421 }
422
423 *node = NULL;
424 return NULL;
425}
426
427struct marker *get_marker_label(struct node *tree, const char *label,
428 struct node **node, struct property **prop)
429{
430 struct marker *m;
431 struct property *p;
432 struct node *c;
433
434 *node = tree;
435
436 for_each_property(tree, p) {
437 *prop = p;
438 m = p->val.markers;
439 for_each_marker_of_type(m, LABEL)
440 if (streq(m->ref, label))
441 return m;
442 }
443
444 for_each_child(tree, c) {
445 m = get_marker_label(c, label, node, prop);
446 if (m)
447 return m;
448 }
449
450 *prop = NULL;
451 *node = NULL;
452 return NULL;
453}
454
455struct node *get_subnode(struct node *node, const char *nodename)
456{
457 struct node *child;
458
459 for_each_child(node, child)
460 if (streq(child->name, nodename))
461 return child;
462
463 return NULL;
464}
465
466struct node *get_node_by_path(struct node *tree, const char *path)
467{
468 const char *p;
469 struct node *child;
470
471 if (!path || ! (*path)) {
472 if (tree->deleted)
473 return NULL;
474 return tree;
475 }
476
477 while (path[0] == '/')
478 path++;
479
480 p = strchr(path, '/');
481
482 for_each_child(tree, child) {
483 if (p && strneq(path, child->name, p-path))
484 return get_node_by_path(child, p+1);
485 else if (!p && streq(path, child->name))
486 return child;
487 }
488
489 return NULL;
490}
491
492struct node *get_node_by_label(struct node *tree, const char *label)
493{
494 struct node *child, *node;
495 struct label *l;
496
497 assert(label && (strlen(label) > 0));
498
499 for_each_label(tree->labels, l)
500 if (streq(l->label, label))
501 return tree;
502
503 for_each_child(tree, child) {
504 node = get_node_by_label(child, label);
505 if (node)
506 return node;
507 }
508
509 return NULL;
510}
511
512struct node *get_node_by_phandle(struct node *tree, cell_t phandle)
513{
514 struct node *child, *node;
515
516 assert((phandle != 0) && (phandle != -1));
517
518 if (tree->phandle == phandle) {
519 if (tree->deleted)
520 return NULL;
521 return tree;
522 }
523
524 for_each_child(tree, child) {
525 node = get_node_by_phandle(child, phandle);
526 if (node)
527 return node;
528 }
529
530 return NULL;
531}
532
533struct node *get_node_by_ref(struct node *tree, const char *ref)
534{
535 if (streq(ref, "/"))
536 return tree;
537 else if (ref[0] == '/')
538 return get_node_by_path(tree, ref);
539 else
540 return get_node_by_label(tree, ref);
541}
542
543cell_t get_node_phandle(struct node *root, struct node *node)
544{
545 static cell_t phandle = 1; /* FIXME: ick, static local */
546
547 if ((node->phandle != 0) && (node->phandle != -1))
548 return node->phandle;
549
550 while (get_node_by_phandle(root, phandle))
551 phandle++;
552
553 node->phandle = phandle;
554
555 if (!get_property(node, "linux,phandle")
556 && (phandle_format & PHANDLE_LEGACY))
557 add_property(node,
558 build_property("linux,phandle",
559 data_append_cell(empty_data, phandle)));
560
561 if (!get_property(node, "phandle")
562 && (phandle_format & PHANDLE_EPAPR))
563 add_property(node,
564 build_property("phandle",
565 data_append_cell(empty_data, phandle)));
566
567 /* If the node *does* have a phandle property, we must
568 * be dealing with a self-referencing phandle, which will be
569 * fixed up momentarily in the caller */
570
571 return node->phandle;
572}
573
574uint32_t guess_boot_cpuid(struct node *tree)
575{
576 struct node *cpus, *bootcpu;
577 struct property *reg;
578
579 cpus = get_node_by_path(tree, "/cpus");
580 if (!cpus)
581 return 0;
582
583
584 bootcpu = cpus->children;
585 if (!bootcpu)
586 return 0;
587
588 reg = get_property(bootcpu, "reg");
589 if (!reg || (reg->val.len != sizeof(uint32_t)))
590 return 0;
591
592 /* FIXME: Sanity check node? */
593
594 return propval_cell(reg);
595}
596
597static int cmp_reserve_info(const void *ax, const void *bx)
598{
599 const struct reserve_info *a, *b;
600
601 a = *((const struct reserve_info * const *)ax);
602 b = *((const struct reserve_info * const *)bx);
603
604 if (a->address < b->address)
605 return -1;
606 else if (a->address > b->address)
607 return 1;
608 else if (a->size < b->size)
609 return -1;
610 else if (a->size > b->size)
611 return 1;
612 else
613 return 0;
614}
615
616static void sort_reserve_entries(struct dt_info *dti)
617{
618 struct reserve_info *ri, **tbl;
619 int n = 0, i = 0;
620
621 for (ri = dti->reservelist;
622 ri;
623 ri = ri->next)
624 n++;
625
626 if (n == 0)
627 return;
628
629 tbl = xmalloc(n * sizeof(*tbl));
630
631 for (ri = dti->reservelist;
632 ri;
633 ri = ri->next)
634 tbl[i++] = ri;
635
636 qsort(tbl, n, sizeof(*tbl), cmp_reserve_info);
637
638 dti->reservelist = tbl[0];
639 for (i = 0; i < (n-1); i++)
640 tbl[i]->next = tbl[i+1];
641 tbl[n-1]->next = NULL;
642
643 free(tbl);
644}
645
646static int cmp_prop(const void *ax, const void *bx)
647{
648 const struct property *a, *b;
649
650 a = *((const struct property * const *)ax);
651 b = *((const struct property * const *)bx);
652
653 return strcmp(a->name, b->name);
654}
655
656static void sort_properties(struct node *node)
657{
658 int n = 0, i = 0;
659 struct property *prop, **tbl;
660
661 for_each_property_withdel(node, prop)
662 n++;
663
664 if (n == 0)
665 return;
666
667 tbl = xmalloc(n * sizeof(*tbl));
668
669 for_each_property_withdel(node, prop)
670 tbl[i++] = prop;
671
672 qsort(tbl, n, sizeof(*tbl), cmp_prop);
673
674 node->proplist = tbl[0];
675 for (i = 0; i < (n-1); i++)
676 tbl[i]->next = tbl[i+1];
677 tbl[n-1]->next = NULL;
678
679 free(tbl);
680}
681
682static int cmp_subnode(const void *ax, const void *bx)
683{
684 const struct node *a, *b;
685
686 a = *((const struct node * const *)ax);
687 b = *((const struct node * const *)bx);
688
689 return strcmp(a->name, b->name);
690}
691
692static void sort_subnodes(struct node *node)
693{
694 int n = 0, i = 0;
695 struct node *subnode, **tbl;
696
697 for_each_child_withdel(node, subnode)
698 n++;
699
700 if (n == 0)
701 return;
702
703 tbl = xmalloc(n * sizeof(*tbl));
704
705 for_each_child_withdel(node, subnode)
706 tbl[i++] = subnode;
707
708 qsort(tbl, n, sizeof(*tbl), cmp_subnode);
709
710 node->children = tbl[0];
711 for (i = 0; i < (n-1); i++)
712 tbl[i]->next_sibling = tbl[i+1];
713 tbl[n-1]->next_sibling = NULL;
714
715 free(tbl);
716}
717
718static void sort_node(struct node *node)
719{
720 struct node *c;
721
722 sort_properties(node);
723 sort_subnodes(node);
724 for_each_child_withdel(node, c)
725 sort_node(c);
726}
727
728void sort_tree(struct dt_info *dti)
729{
730 sort_reserve_entries(dti);
731 sort_node(dti->dt);
732}

734/* utility helper to avoid code duplication */
735static struct node *build_and_name_child_node(struct node *parent, char *name)
736{
737 struct node *node;
738
739 node = build_node(NULL, NULL);
740 name_node(node, xstrdup(name));
741 add_child(parent, node);
742
743 return node;
744}
745
746static struct node *build_root_node(struct node *dt, char *name)
747{
748 struct node *an;
749
750 an = get_subnode(dt, name);
751 if (!an)
752 an = build_and_name_child_node(dt, name);
753
754 if (!an)
755 die("Could not build root node /%s\n", name);
756
757 return an;
758}
759
760static bool any_label_tree(struct dt_info *dti, struct node *node)
761{
762 struct node *c;
763
764 if (node->labels)
765 return true;
766
767 for_each_child(node, c)
768 if (any_label_tree(dti, c))
769 return true;
770
771 return false;
772}
773
774static void generate_label_tree_internal(struct dt_info *dti,
775 struct node *an, struct node *node,
776 bool allocph)
777{
778 struct node *dt = dti->dt;
779 struct node *c;
780 struct property *p;
781 struct label *l;
782
783 /* if there are labels */
784 if (node->labels) {
785
786 /* now add the label in the node */
787 for_each_label(node->labels, l) {
788
789 /* check whether the label already exists */
790 p = get_property(an, l->label);
791 if (p) {
792 fprintf(stderr, "WARNING: label %s already"
793 " exists in /%s", l->label,
794 an->name);
795 continue;
796 }
797
798 /* insert it */
799 p = build_property(l->label,
800 data_copy_mem(node->fullpath,
801 strlen(node->fullpath) + 1));
802 add_property(an, p);
803 }
804
805 /* force allocation of a phandle for this node */
806 if (allocph)
807 (void)get_node_phandle(dt, node);
808 }
809
810 for_each_child(node, c)
811 generate_label_tree_internal(dti, an, c, allocph);
812}
813
814static bool any_fixup_tree(struct dt_info *dti, struct node *node)
815{
816 struct node *c;
817 struct property *prop;
818 struct marker *m;
819
820 for_each_property(node, prop) {
821 m = prop->val.markers;
822 for_each_marker_of_type(m, REF_PHANDLE) {
823 if (!get_node_by_ref(dti->dt, m->ref))
824 return true;
825 }
826 }
827
828 for_each_child(node, c) {
829 if (any_fixup_tree(dti, c))
830 return true;
831 }
832
833 return false;
834}
835
836static void add_fixup_entry(struct dt_info *dti, struct node *fn,
837 struct node *node, struct property *prop,
838 struct marker *m)
839{
840 char *entry;
841
842 /* m->ref can only be a REF_PHANDLE, but check anyway */
843 assert(m->type == REF_PHANDLE);
844
845 /* there shouldn't be any ':' in the arguments */
846 if (strchr(node->fullpath, ':') || strchr(prop->name, ':'))
847 die("arguments should not contain ':'\n");
848
849 xasprintf(&entry, "%s:%s:%u",
850 node->fullpath, prop->name, m->offset);
851 append_to_property(fn, m->ref, entry, strlen(entry) + 1);
852
853 free(entry);
854}
855
856static void generate_fixups_tree_internal(struct dt_info *dti,
857 struct node *fn,
858 struct node *node)
859{
860 struct node *dt = dti->dt;
861 struct node *c;
862 struct property *prop;
863 struct marker *m;
864 struct node *refnode;
865
866 for_each_property(node, prop) {
867 m = prop->val.markers;
868 for_each_marker_of_type(m, REF_PHANDLE) {
869 refnode = get_node_by_ref(dt, m->ref);
870 if (!refnode)
871 add_fixup_entry(dti, fn, node, prop, m);
872 }
873 }
874
875 for_each_child(node, c)
876 generate_fixups_tree_internal(dti, fn, c);
877}
878
879static bool any_local_fixup_tree(struct dt_info *dti, struct node *node)
880{
881 struct node *c;
882 struct property *prop;
883 struct marker *m;
884
885 for_each_property(node, prop) {
886 m = prop->val.markers;
887 for_each_marker_of_type(m, REF_PHANDLE) {
888 if (get_node_by_ref(dti->dt, m->ref))
889 return true;
890 }
891 }
892
893 for_each_child(node, c) {
894 if (any_local_fixup_tree(dti, c))
895 return true;
896 }
897
898 return false;
899}
900
901static void add_local_fixup_entry(struct dt_info *dti,
902 struct node *lfn, struct node *node,
903 struct property *prop, struct marker *m,
904 struct node *refnode)
905{
906 struct node *wn, *nwn; /* local fixup node, walk node, new */
907 fdt32_t value_32;
908 char **compp;
909 int i, depth;
910
911 /* walk back retreiving depth */
912 depth = 0;
913 for (wn = node; wn; wn = wn->parent)
914 depth++;
915
916 /* allocate name array */
917 compp = xmalloc(sizeof(*compp) * depth);
918
919 /* store names in the array */
920 for (wn = node, i = depth - 1; wn; wn = wn->parent, i--)
921 compp[i] = wn->name;
922
923 /* walk the path components creating nodes if they don't exist */
924 for (wn = lfn, i = 1; i < depth; i++, wn = nwn) {
925 /* if no node exists, create it */
926 nwn = get_subnode(wn, compp[i]);
927 if (!nwn)
928 nwn = build_and_name_child_node(wn, compp[i]);
929 }
930
931 free(compp);
932
933 value_32 = cpu_to_fdt32(m->offset);
934 append_to_property(wn, prop->name, &value_32, sizeof(value_32));
935}
936
937static void generate_local_fixups_tree_internal(struct dt_info *dti,
938 struct node *lfn,
939 struct node *node)
940{
941 struct node *dt = dti->dt;
942 struct node *c;
943 struct property *prop;
944 struct marker *m;
945 struct node *refnode;
946
947 for_each_property(node, prop) {
948 m = prop->val.markers;
949 for_each_marker_of_type(m, REF_PHANDLE) {
950 refnode = get_node_by_ref(dt, m->ref);
951 if (refnode)
952 add_local_fixup_entry(dti, lfn, node, prop, m, refnode);
953 }
954 }
955
956 for_each_child(node, c)
957 generate_local_fixups_tree_internal(dti, lfn, c);
958}
959
960void generate_label_tree(struct dt_info *dti, char *name, bool allocph)
961{
962 if (!any_label_tree(dti, dti->dt))
963 return;
964 generate_label_tree_internal(dti, build_root_node(dti->dt, name),
965 dti->dt, allocph);
966}
967
968void generate_fixups_tree(struct dt_info *dti, char *name)
969{
970 if (!any_fixup_tree(dti, dti->dt))
971 return;
972 generate_fixups_tree_internal(dti, build_root_node(dti->dt, name),
973 dti->dt);
974}
975
976void generate_local_fixups_tree(struct dt_info *dti, char *name)
977{
978 if (!any_local_fixup_tree(dti, dti->dt))
979 return;
980 generate_local_fixups_tree_internal(dti, build_root_node(dti->dt, name),
981 dti->dt);
982}
